# Use [Homebrew](http://brew.sh/)

## To easily install stuff

While you are developing software you will likely need to install a number of tools, frameworks and applications. The easiest way to do this is to use a package manager.

- Open Spotlight (⌘ Space), type `terminal` and press Return
- In the Terminal window that pops up, type the following: 

```bash
/usr/bin/ruby -e "$(curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Homebrew/install/master/install)"
```

---

# Keep Homebrew Happy

Do this semi-regularly:

- Keep Homebrew up to date: `brew update`
- Keep Homebrew healthy: `brew doctor`
  - This may give you some information to act on, which you should
- Keep Homebrew slim: `brew cleanup`

